word_mean_info__list.difference: 正式用词，多指以某事或活动达到预期目的而告终。
与complete基本同义，着重圆满地结束或完成已着手的事。
正式用词，强调一个过程的完成；也可指依靠努力达到一定目的，或取得一定的结果。
强调有一个空间和时间的限度，届时必须终止。书面语用词。
侧重指完成预定的任务或使某事完善，补足缺少的部分等。
最普通用词，着重事情的完成。也指某种活动因达到目的而自然结束或由于某种原因而突然中止。
普通用词，着重行为的终止或结束，不强调其目的。
与object基本同义，但语义更广泛，指具体或很快能达到的目的，也可指军事目标。书面用词。
从本义“靶子”引申而来，侧重比较具体而明确的目标，但常指短期目标。
指射击的靶，军事攻击目标。引申指被攻击、批评或潮笑的目标。
强调个人或需求而决定的目标、目的。
普通用词，既指以坚决、审慎的行动去达到的目的，又指心中渴望要实际的目标。
指心目中怀着的某种目的，强调结果而非过程。较正式用词。
指经过考虑和选择，需经坚持不懈的努力奋斗才能达到的最终目标。

bilingual.source: And that's the end of the six o'clock news.
But Ho's good work came to a sudden end.
bilingual.target: 但是何的好工作突然结束了。

bilingual.source: End your talk by summarising your points.
bilingual.target: 通过总结你的观点结束你的演讲。

bilingual.source: It celebrates the end of racial inequality in the country.
bilingual.target: 它庆祝该国种族不平等的结束。

bilingual.source: End your talk by encouraging your audience to become “greener”.
bilingual.target: 通过鼓励听众变得更环保来结束你的演讲。

bilingual.source: I can't believe the first week is coming to an end.
bilingual.target: 我不敢相信第一周就要结束了。

bilingual.source: By the end of this unit, you will make a plan.
bilingual.target: 在本单元结束时，你将制定一个计划。

bilingual.source: The end of junior high school is the beginning of a new life.
bilingual.target: 初中的结束是新生活的开始。

list.abstract: 词语end是结束；末端；目标；死亡；尽头的意思。词性有三种：名词n.[C]及物动词vt.不及物动词vi.
end，日本漫画《妖精的尾巴》及其衍生作品中的角色，是暗黑公会“冥府之门”的核心与创立者杰尔夫创造出的最强恶魔-炎之恶魔，拥有可毁灭掉世界的力量。 400年前end曾与火龙王伊格尼尔有一战，但由于某些不回明原因，伊格尼尔没能消灭end，在随后的400年里end以书的形态存在。

yingyinNormal.en: The End of the Holiday
yingyinNormal.zh: 结束旅行

yingyinNormal.en: I can end Dunbar's campaign. We can end it today.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我可以终结邓巴的竞选，今天就结束掉。

yingyinNormal.en: The End of the Holiday
yingyinNormal.zh: 第4季第39集《结束旅行》

yingyinNormal.en: Look it's the end of the date, I'm standing there.
yingyinNormal.zh: 约会结束了，我站在那里。

yingyinNormal.en: And end this war before it ever begins.
yingyinNormal.zh: 从而，在灭绝变种人开始前，结束这场战争。

yingyinNormal.en: Please hold all questions till the end of the presentation.
yingyinNormal.zh: 请等演讲结束后再提问。

yingyinNormal.en: And then Daddy came and rescued her. The end.
yingyinNormal.zh: 最后是爸爸把他救出来。故事结束了。

yingyinNormal.en: They shot Nick Fury. And it won't end there.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他们刺杀了尼克弗瑞，事情没有到此结束。

yingyinNormal.en: And when this rock disappears, that Truce will end.
yingyinNormal.zh: 等和平岩消失的时候，休战期也就结束了。

yingyinNormal.en: Thank you, that's the end of my amazingly impossible circus.
yingyinNormal.zh: 谢谢，我的神奇的不可能的马戏团表演要结束了。

yingyinNormal.en: That's the end. Goodbye children. Happy Christmas. Happy Christmas everybody.
yingyinNormal.zh: 结束了孩子们，圣诞快乐！祝大家圣诞节快乐！

yingyinNormal.en: It's a relationship that is about to end and when this will end you will never see this person again.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这段关系就要结束了结束之后，你再也不会和这个人见面。

yingyinNormal.en: Of course, the end of our combat mission in Afghanistan doesn't mean the end of challenges to our security.
yingyinNormal.zh: 当然，我们在阿富汗战斗任务的结束，并不意味着对我们安全挑战的结束。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm dedicating my life to your deaths. This war will not end.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我会穷尽一生找你索命，这场战争不会结束。

yingyinNormal.en: The end of freshman year, I kind of dated the swim team captain.
yingyinNormal.zh: 一年级快结束那年，我跟游泳队队长约过会。

yingyinNormal.en: And you don't think that person has the right to end his or her life?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你不认为这样的人有权利结束自己的生命吗？

yingyinNormal.en: Come on, I didn't want anyone to feel bad at the end of the game.
yingyinNormal.zh: 拜托，我不想让任何人在游戏结束的时候伤心啊。

yingyinNormal.en: Absolem? Why are you upside down? I've come to the end of this life.
yingyinNormal.zh: 亚伯索伦？你怎么挂在那里？我的生命就快结束了。

yingyinNormal.en: May her powers signify the end of tyranny and the beginning of a new era.
yingyinNormal.zh: 愿她的力量意味着暴政的结束和一个新时代的开启。

yingyinNormal.en: I did not see that common twist ending. My stories never end like that.
yingyinNormal.zh: 没有出人意料的结局, 我的故事从来不会这样结束。

examination_example.sentence: Before it <highlight>ends</highlight>, it will likely change the life course and character of a generation of young adults.

examination_example.sentence: While 59% of "unretire" said it would be tied to making <highlight>ends</highlight> meet.

examination_example.sentence: Feel that is enough to make <highlight>ends</highlight> meet.

examination_example.sentence: Many people will be having a very hard time making <highlight>ends</highlight> meet.

examination_example.sentence: But too often we take this process too far and <highlight>end</highlight> up suppressing emotions, especially negative ones.

examination_example.sentence: They suggest beauty should not be defined by looks that <highlight>end</highlight> up impinging on health.

examination_example.sentence: What is important is not truth, but publication, which has become almost an <highlight>end</highlight> in itself.

examination_example.sentence: A society designed with other <highlight>ends</highlight> in mind could yield strikingly different circumstances for the future of labor and leisure.

examination_example.sentence: Overfishing in the pristine waters could see king penguin populations pushed to the brink of extinction by the <highlight>end</highlight> of the century.

examination_example.sentence: Morgan said last week that he would retire at the <highlight>end</highlight> of January.

examination_example.sentence: This is to teach children a lesson at the <highlight>end</highlight> of the program.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这是为了在节目最后给孩子们上一课。

examination_example.sentence: It emerged towards the <highlight>end</highlight> of the 1980s as a purely text-based medium.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它在20世纪80年代末作为一种纯文本媒体出现。

examination_example.sentence: Marconi was really interested in only one thing: the extension of mobile, personal, long­-distance communication to the <highlight>ends</highlight> of the earth.

word_usage.usage: in the end后面不能接of短语，该短语的意思是“最后，终于”，相当于finally/at last。

at the end of 后面可以接表示时间或地点的名词，意思是“在…末端”或“在…结尾”。
示例： My son hopes to become a lawyer at the end of next year.
我儿子希望明年年底成为一名律师。
end用作名词指时间或动作的末尾、结束。故事、小说、电影、戏剧等的结尾、结局才用ending。

by the end of表示“在…尽头”，“到...结束时”，主句一般用完成时态。
示例：到1980年底，他已完成了他的巨著。
误 He finished his great works by the end of 1980.
正 He had finished his great works by the end of 1980.

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 普通用词, 着重行为的终止或结束, 不强调其目的。
正式用词, 多指以某事或活动达到预期目的而告终。
最普通用词, 着重事情的完成。也指某种活动因达到目的而自然结束或由于某种原因而突然中止。
从本义"靶子"引申而来, 侧重比较具体而明确的目标, 但常指短期目标。如：My first aim is to receive a complete and good education.(我的第一个目标是接受完整和良好的教育。)
指心目中怀着的某种目的, 强调结果而非过程。较正式用词。如：My chief end is to serve my country and my people.(我的首要目标是为国为民服务。)
指经过考虑和选择, 需经坚持不懈的努力奋斗才能达到的最终目标。如：The goal of her desire is to be a singer.(她渴望成为一名歌唱家。)
强调个人或需求而决定的目标、目的。如：Her sole object in life is to become a travel writer.(她人生的唯一目标就是当游记作家。)
objective 与 object 基本同义, 但语义更广泛, 指具体或很快能达到的目的, 也可指军事目标。书面用词。

examination_example.sentence: Finally, the FBI received a tip that the stolen document was located very close to Washington, D. C. Their art crime team recovered the letter but were unable to press charges because the time of limitations had <highlight>ended</highlight>.

examination_example.sentence: While two of these ships sank, they were all designed with double hulls (船体) believed to make them "unsinkable", perhaps a mistaken idea that led to the Titanic's and the Britannic's tragic <highlight>end</highlight>.

examination_example.sentence: "These clouds can be huge. Some of them stretch hundreds of kilometres from <highlight>end</highlight> to <highlight>end</highlight>," NASA officials said.

examination_example.sentence: He says the question is not whether we can, but whether we should, and to what <highlight>end</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他说，问题不在于我们是否能够，而在于我们是否应该，以及目的是什么。

examination_example.sentence: To that <highlight>end</highlight>, they have been studying how other species deal with low gravity, specifically focusing on mice.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 为此，他们一直在研究其他物种如何应对低重力，特别是老鼠。

word_usage.usage:
at the end of 后面可以接表示时间或地点的名词，意思是“在…末端”或“在…结尾”。
示例： My son hopes to become a lawyer at the end of next year.
我儿子希望明年年底成为一名律师。

by the end of表示“在…尽头”，“到...结束时”，主句一般用完成时态。
示例：到1980年底，他已完成了他的巨著。
误 He finished his great works by the end of 1980.
正 He had finished his great works by the end of 1980.
end用作名词指时间或动作的末尾、结束。故事、小说、电影、戏剧等的结尾、结局才用ending。
in the end后面不能接of短语，该短语的意思是“最后，终于”，相当于finally/at last。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 普通用词，着重行为的终止或结束，不强调其目的。
正式用词，多指以某事或活动达到预期目的而告终。
最普通用词，着重事情的完成。也指某种活动因达到目的而自然结束或由于某种原因而突然中止。
